to go through, analyze, think, read the file,

258
00:10:44,559 --> 00:10:46,479
that all happened in a sub-agent

259
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,679
outside the context of the main agent,

260
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:52,400
allowing us to efficiently divvy up the task.

261
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,159
It allowed us to frame a prompt

262
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:55,359
for a different sub-agent

263
00:10:55,359 --> 00:10:58,239
and also keep that context isolated.

264
00:10:58,239 --> 00:11:00,000
Those are some of the big advantages.

265
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,280
And we'll go through more of them later.

266
00:11:01,919 --> 00:11:03,919
And that whole file has been written here

267
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:06,400
to review.md that we can open up.

268
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,280
And this is a project review that's got through.

269
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:12,000
Oh, there's a critical security issue.

270
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:17,200
This often seems to happen with the sub-agents.

271
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,520
I think we experienced this ourselves before.

272
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,599
This fact that the sub-agents tend to think

273
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:22,559
that there's an issue

274
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:25,359
that .emv isn't in .gitignore,

275
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,359
but the key is visible in the repository.

276
00:11:29,359 --> 00:11:31,919
I suppose that is a security issue in some ways,

277
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:32,960
but only with people

278
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,640
who have direct repository access,

279
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,760
which is only me.

280
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,200
Anyways, this happened.

281
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,239
We've got our review.

282
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:39,840
The sub-agent worked.

283
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,440
That is very interesting.

284
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,559
What else can we do?

285
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:44,320
You know exactly what I want to do.

286
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,559
I want to have Codex be the thing

287
00:11:46,559 --> 00:11:47,599
that does the review.

288
00:11:47,599 --> 00:11:49,359
I want to have a different AI.

289
00:11:49,919 --> 00:11:52,719
Let's give that a shot in the next video.

